info.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 14 at 2:05AM PDT until March 14 at 10:00PM PDT by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM THIS MORNING TO 10 PM PDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...South winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. The strongest winds are expected in the hills. * WHERE...Central Coast, and the Santa Ynez, Southern Salinas and Cuyama Valleys. * WHEN...From 6 AM this morning to 10 PM PDT this evening. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Roadways may be affected by gusty cross winds, including Highways 1, 41, 46, 101, and 246. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
